    comment "New Concept of the following classes (and their ancestors):
* EqnData
* StoreSol
* WriteResults
* DOF-Object (

The Objective is the following:
* Make the WriteResults-class more flexible (pull-mechanism, region-awareness, named-dofs, etc.)
* Make the definition of the equation-numbers dependend on the single integrators, i.e. each integrator may define its own set of

In Case of Adaptivity we have to distinguish two cases:
1.) Fixed (anistotropic) approximiation scheme per integrator/reigion (e.g. 3D-plates)
2.) Per element change in approximation order due to hp-refinement

In the first case it is sufficient to have one fixed result-ansatz-dof pair per region and integrator, whereas in the second case each element must be assigned a 
distinct ansatz dof. In the sedond case we can either assign each Elem an own approximation scheme element or we may only refer to a set of different 
ansatz dofs, which is held by the Domain class. The advantage of the latter one is, that only a number is needed to reference a nodel ansatz set, whereas
in the first case each element needs a complete object for approximation. The question is, who determines the h/p-refinement?"
